snippet.textDisplay: MatPat and Gus's comments were very well said. As viewers I think we put to much pressure on YouTube as do the creators and brands to satisfy us specifically. There definitely needs to be more transparency, but YouTube can only do so much. As a viewer, what I hope to see in the next decade is better communication between all four sides and the incorporation of careers to do so. Hire people specifically to listen to the viewers, creators, and brands and report directly to YouTube's higher ups to figure out what will ultimately work for everyone. I don't believe the current Customer Service platform sends our criticism or suggestions to those who could incorporate them, and I think it would make for a better platform if this was introduced.

snippet.textDisplay: Youtubers are honestly so smart and seem to be on the same page with what a lot of creators and viewers feel about how Youtube has changed for the worse over the years. It's disheartening that Youtube doesn't seem to listen to its creators and instead focuses on celebrities on the platform, advertisers and family friendly content, because the creators really do know what's up and Youtube should be listening to and celebrating the people who built this platform and cultivated our community. It's frustrating that "traditional media" still doesn't take youtubers seriously, it feels like we're yelling into a void at this point while the platform slowly goes downhill.
